author: psiwebtn
title: On This Date
text:
On This Date Monday, October 19, 2015 
October 17, 1941 - Touchdowns from Billy Abromitis and Johnny Urban, and an extra point from Jackie Costello allow Tamaqua to hold off Mahanoy City for a 13-12 victory. Abromitis reaches the end zone on a 14-yard run in the second quarter to tie the contest while Urbanâ€™s one-yard plunge in the third frame gives the Blue and White, coached by Charley Schaeffer, the lead for good. The winners also receive a key interception by Steigerwalt in the red zone to stop a Mahanoy drive.
